Symmetry: “Neural networks for neutrinos” (Pierre Baldi quoted)
January 24, 2018 “All these big physics experiments are really very similar at the machine learning level,” says Pierre Baldi, a computer scientist at the University of California, Irvine. “It’s all images associated with these complex, very expensive detectors, and deep learning is the best method for extracting signal against some background noise.” 
Read the full story at Symmetry Magazine.
